# ATR CODEOWNERS
#
# Reviewer routing for the Agent Threat Rules canonical repository.
# Authority and review obligations follow TSC-CHARTER.md §5.
#
# Layered fallthrough: the most specific match wins. Generic patterns
# below catch anything not covered above.

# === Governance ===
# All governance documents require TSC review. BDFL holds transitional
# authority per TSC-CHARTER.md §2.3.
GOVERNANCE.md                  @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
TSC-CHARTER.md                 @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
TRADEMARK.md                   @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
docs/BDFL-charter.md           @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
ANNOUNCEMENT-*.md              @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
BRAND.md                       @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
TSC-ONBOARDING.md              @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345

# === Specification ===
SPEC.md                        @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
spec/atr-schema.yaml           @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
spec/internet-drafts/**        @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345

# === Conformance suite ===
# Suite content and runner code require TSC review (Charter §2.1.d).
conformance/**                 @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345

# === Single source of truth ===
# Edits to stats.json or its sync mechanism affect every derived
# surface; require TSC + BDFL review.
stats.json                     @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
scripts/sync-stats.ts          @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345

# === Meetings ===
# Minutes and agendas are authored by the meeting's nominated
# minute-taker; the TSC team approves.
meetings/**                    @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345

# === CI safety ===
# Changes to the safety gate, publish pipeline, and quality CI need
# both TSC review and BDFL approval.
.github/workflows/**           @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
.github/CODEOWNERS             @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
scripts/check-rules-safety.ts  @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345

# === Rules ===
# Rule PRs are reviewed by the rules team; CI quality gate is the
# primary authority. TSC review is requested only when a rule is
# flagged `needs-tsc-review` by a reviewer.
rules/**                       @eeee2345

# === Top-level project meta ===
README.md                      @eeee2345
CHANGELOG.md                   @eeee2345
CITATION.cff                   @eeee2345
package.json                   @eeee2345
LICENSE                        @Agent-Threat-Rule/tsc @eeee2345
